The paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves optimizing a set of "phantom" object classes, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with semantic descriptions of object classes, which falls under the category of natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves optimization and performance evaluation, which are common themes in computational linguistics, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with benchmark datasets, which is a common theme in multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category.
